<div class="safety-tips">
	<div class="tips" id="wash-hands">
		<h3>Wash your hands often</h3>
		<ul class="tips-list">
			<li class="tipsitem">
        		<a>Wash your hands with soap and water for at least 20 seconds especially after you have been in a public place, or after blowing your nose, coughing, or sneezing</a>
      		</li>
			<li class="tipsitem">
				<a>Utilize hand sanitizer when soap and water are not available</a>
			</li>
			<li class="tipsitem">
				<a>Avoid touching any part of your face with unwashed hands</a>
			</li>
		</ul>
		<a class="link" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=seA1wbXUQTs" target="_blank">Click here to get tutorial</a>
	</div>
	<div class="tips" id="avoid-contact">
		<h4>Avoid close contact</h4>
		<ul class="tips-list">
			<li class="tipsitems">
				<a>Avoid close contact with people who are sick, even inside your home. If possible, maintain 6 feet between the person who is sick and other household members</a>
			</li>
			<li class ="tipsitems">
				<a>Stay at least 6 feet apart from other people</a>
			</li>
			<li class="tipsitems">
				<a>Stay out of crowded places and do not hang out in big groups, try to only meet people from your household</a>
			</li>
			<li class="tipsitems">
				<a>Only go out to get necessities in order to minimize risk</a>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="tips" id="mask">
		<h3>Always cover your mouth and nose with a cloth face cover when around others</h3>
		<ul class="tips-list">
			<li class="tipsitem">
				<a>Everyone should wear a cloth face cover when they have to go out in public to prevent the spread of the Covid-19 virus</a>
			</li>
			<li class="tipsitem">
				<a>Do not use facemasks that are meant for healthcare workers, like N95 mask or any type of surgical mask, as these items are currently in shortage</a>
			</li>
			<li class="tipsitem">
				<a>Remember to always wash your cloth face cover after going out in public</a>
			</li>
		</ul>
		<a class="link" href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/diy-cloth-face-coverings.html" target="_blank">Click here to know about the proper way to wear a face cover and how to make your own cloth face cover</a>
	</div>
	<div class="tips" id="cough">
		<h4>Cover coughs and sneezes</h4>
		<ul class ="tips-list">
			<li class="tipsitems">
				<a>Remember to always cough or sneeze with a tissue or use the inside of your elbow</a>
			</li>
			<li class="tipsitems">
				<a>Throw all used tissues in the trash, do not keep them around</a>
			</li>
			<li class="tipsitems">
				<a>Immediately wash your hands with soap and water or sanitize with hand sanitizer, more information on this area is provided above</a>
			</li>
		</ul>
		<div>
		<a class="links" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J2jbEetZ8G4" target="_blank">Click here to know more about proper way of covering cough or sneeze</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="tips" id="clean">
		<h3>Clean and disinfect</h3>
		<ul class="tips-list">
			<li class= "tipsitem">
				<a>Clean and disinfect all surfaces regularly, things like tables, doorknobs, light switches, phones, etc</a>
			</li>
			<li class="tipsitem">
				<a>You should clean the dirty surfaces with soap or detergent prior to disinfection</a>
			</li>
			<li class= "tipsitem">
				<a>Use a household disinfectant, using the EPA-registered goods are recommended</a>
			</li>
		</ul>
		<a class="link" href="https://www.epa.gov/pesticide-registration/list-n-disinfectants-use-against-sars-cov-2" target="_blank">Click here to find about about EPA-registered items</a>
	</div>
</div>

